Privacy Policy
This privacy policy (“Policy”) is intended to inform you about how your Personal Data will be handled by Bamboo Connected BV (“Firsty“, “we”, “us” or “our”), and sets out the information including personal information detailed below relating to you or which you provide to us (“Personal Data“) that will be collected and processed by Firsty and/or on its behalf by its third party service providers.
We are required to give you this information, including to inform you about your data protection rights, under the General Data Protection Regulation (EU) 2016/679 (“GDPR”).This Policy will be regularly reviewed and may be amended and updated from time to time as necessary. Any updates to this Policy will be posted on the website and/or communicated by e-mail
1. Firsty as data controller
Bamboo Connected BV (Firsty), with its registered office at Bilderdijkkade 40-4, 1053VE Amsterdam, Netherlands, is responsible for the collection and processing of your personal data both via the web as via the Firsty application app in its capacity as controller.
Firsty is committed to respecting your fundamental right to the protection of your Personal Data and this Policy is intended to inform you about the processing of your Personal Data by us.
2. Types of Personal Data we process about you
‍
Customer Data:
When you install an e-SIM or data plan we will process your full name; country of residence; current location; residential address; telephone number; payment information; e-mail address; and other details relating to you when you interact with us regarding the purchase of an e-SIM.
Website Usage and Device Data: When you visit our application, or our website, we will process your visits and interactions with our website including which webpages you visit, time and date of access, what you click on, when you perform these actions;
Your device data including your IP address, location data, device type and language, browser type and other related information; and Any linked websites that you access through the website.
Most of this Personal Data is collected using cookies on the Website. Please see our Cookies Policy for more information about how the website uses cookies.
3. Sources of your Personal Data
During the course of our contractual relationship with you or when you visit our website or application, we will collect Personal Data either:
(1) directly from you, or
(2) indirectly from third parties (for example, once you have contracted for our services, through our affiliates or travel agencies).When you browse on our website, different cookies and other tracking devices may be installed on your device, asset out in our Cookies Policy.
4. For what purpose and on what legal basis do we process personal data? Legal basis Purposes Data
Compliance with a Legal Obligation Firsty may process your Personal Data where it is necessary to comply with legal obligations to which we are subject under European Union and/or applicable laws, including but not limited to safeguarding and complying with law enforcement requests. Customer Data Website data
5. With whom do we share Personal Data?
Depending on the Purpose for which we process your Personal Data, we may share such Personal Data with some or all of the following recipients to the extent necessary:
Telecommunications service providers: Service providers located in the appropriate jurisdiction;
Regulatory authorities and law enforcement agencies: Where we are under a duty to disclose or share your Personal Data in order to comply with any legal or regulatory obligation or request, such as the Data Protection Commission, or any other applicable authorities.
Third party service providers: We engage third party suppliers who may process your Personal Data on our behalf for the above Purposes. These include administrative services, advertising and communication services, maintenance services, archiving, custody, storage and digitalization services, IT services.
6. International Data Transfers
Users resident in the European Union should note that your Personal Data will be transferred to certain recipients(our external service providers) who are located outside the European Economic Area (“EEA”) in countries with laws and practices that do not contain equivalent data protection rights for your Personal Data.
Where such transfers occur, we ensure that appropriate safeguards are in place by ensuring that: a) transfers do not occur without our prior written authority; and b) that an appropriate transfer mechanism is in place to protect and safeguard your Personal Data.
7. Your data protection rights
Performance of a contract The processing of some of your personal data (first name, last name, country of residence, email address, location, mobile phone number) for this purpose is necessary for the performance of the contract in the context of the creation of a user account, to uniquely identify you.
Also we need to manage the purchase of the e-SIM or data plan that we offer in our App and the payment relating to such products, to calculate and issue charges for services provided to you and review and attend to customer incidents, queries, complaints or requests relating to our products and services.
Customer Data Website data Legitimate Interest Some personal data elements are processed based on the legitimate interest of to facilitate the use of your e-SIM or data plan, including the administration of your account, and to provide customer care to you, to better understand how our customers use our website to improve it, to tailor products and services to you and, if you consent to direct marketing, to tailor direct marketing, to monitor against and prevent cyber-security issues and unauthorized use of our information, IT systems and/or equipment, if necessary to contact the customer if fraud or identity theft is detected or there are reasonable suspicions of fraud, identity theft or illegal activity, to conduct periodic reviews of our services and carry out satisfaction surveys to evaluate and improve the quality of the service we provide.
Right Information
‍
Right of access You have the right to request access to your personal data. In case you want to exercise this right, Firsty will provide you with an overview of the personal data that is processed about you. You are also entitled to receive a free copy of the processed data in an intelligible form. Firsty may charge reasonable fees to cover its administrative costs for any additional copy requested.
8. How long do we keep your Personal Data
We shall not retain your data longer than is necessary to achieve the purpose for which it was collected, in particular with respect to the statutory storage and limitation periods and taking into account the fact that some data must be retained for a certain period of time by virtue of certain laws.
As a former customer, your personal data will be kept for a maximum of two years after you are no longer a customer of Firsty.
For certain categories of data, shorter retention periods apply, such as the data on your communication traffic, which will not be kept longer than twelve months.
9. Children’s Personal Data
In order to users must be either
(i) 18 years old (or the equivalent age as specified by law in your jurisdiction)
(ii) 13 and older if either an emancipated minor, or he/she possess legal parental or guardian consent.
We do not knowingly collect (or knowingly allow any third party to collect) Personal Data from persons under the age of 18.
If we become aware that Personal Data has been collected from a user under the age of 18, we will delete this Personal Data and terminate that individual’s account as quickly as possible.
